# Always Build Locally

When the user asks to build, run, set up, verify, or ship the app, **default to a local workflow** on this machine.

## Do

- Use the project `.venv`, `pip install -r requirements.txt`, and local commands
- Run Streamlit locally (`streamlit run src/ui/app.py`)
- Run `pytest` and smoke tests locally
- Prefer finishing/fixing code so it runs end-to-end locally

## Do not (unless explicitly requested)

- Deploy to remote servers (including IPs in `ip` or similar files)
- Prefer cloud/remote build options when a local path exists
- Ask whether to build locally vs remotely — choose local by default

## Clarifying questions

Only ask about remote/deploy if the user clearly wants production hosting, CI, or a remote machine. Otherwise assume local.
